                            <comment id="16849122" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 27 May 2019 18:34:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hachikuji commented on pull request #6823: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8437&quot; title=&quot;Consumer should wait for api version before checking if offset validation is possible&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8437&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8437&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; Await node api versions before checking if offset validation is possible&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6823&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/6823&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   The consumer should await api version information before determining whether the broker supports offset validation. In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8422&quot; title=&quot;Client should not use old versions of OffsetsForLeaderEpoch&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8422&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8422&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we skip the validation if we don&apos;t have api version information, which means we always skip validation the first time we connect to a node.&lt;/p&gt;

